test_275="Background"
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_276="Potato late blight , a disease caused by the oomycete pathogen Phytophthora infestans , is one of the world ' s most devastating crop diseases ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_277="World - wide losses due to late blight exceed several billion dollars annually [ 1 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_278="Most of the potato cultivars currently grown in the United States are highly susceptible to late blight and control of this disease relies almost exclusively on fungicide applications ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_279="The most effective and environmentally sound way for controlling late blight is to incorporate natural resistance into potato cultivars ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_280="The pedigrees of many potato cultivars currently used in different countries include late blight resistant germplasm derived from Solanum demissum , Solanum andigena , and other wild species ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_281="However , most of the resistance derived from these wild species is controlled by single dominant resistance genes ( R genes ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_282="These R genes are only effective in preventing the development of late blight if the invading P . infestans race contains the corresponding avirulence genes ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_283="This R gene - mediated resistance is often short - lived and is rapidly overcome by new races of the late blight pathogen ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_284="Solanum bulbocastanum ( 2n = 2x = 24 ) is a diploid species that has adapted in the same environment as the late blight pathogen ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_285="This wild species was characterized as possessing durable resistance against P . infestans , even under high disease pressure [ 2 , 3 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_286="Two resistance genes , RB ( Rpi - blb1 ) and Rpi - blb2 , have been cloned from S . bulbocastanum [ 4 - 6 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_287="Both genes confer broad - spectrum resistance against a wide range of known P . infestans races ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_288="Transgenic potato lines containing a single RB gene showed a high - level resistance in the Toluca Valley , Mexico , where the potato fields are naturally intensively infested with the most diversified P . infestans populations [ 7 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_289="Most interestingly , transgenic RB plants did not show total immunity to late blight , but instead showed a marked delay in both onset of symptoms and development of lesions ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= [
    {
        "entity_type": "Pathological_formation",
        "entity_value": "lesions",
        "start_position": 166,
        "end_position": 173
    }
]

test_290="Such rate - limiting resistance may put less selection pressure on the P . infestans populations and protect the durability of this resistance gene ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_291="The RB gene therefore provides an excellent model to study the mechanism of broad - spectrum and rate - limiting disease resistances ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_292="An understanding of the underlying mechanism of this type of resistance is important for developing strategies to breed durable and sustainable disease resistance ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_293="Several genes have been implicated in the regulation of R gene function ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_294="Of these genes , Rar1 and Sgt1 are among the most extensively studied genes ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_295="The Rar1 ( required for Mla12 resistance ) gene was first identified for its essential role in the function of a subset of Mla genes that confer resistance to barley powdery mildew [ 8 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_296="The RAR1 protein contains two highly similar but distinct cysteine - and histidine - rich ( CHORD ) Zn2 + - binding domains and was proposed to play a role in stabilizing R proteins in a confirmation that is implicated in receiving pathogen signals [ 9 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_297="The Sgt1 gene ( suppressor of the G2 allele of skp1 ) is an essential gene with multiple functions in yeast ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_298="SGT1 protein was initially identified as a RAR1 - interacting partner in a yeast two - hybrid screen [ 10 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_299="SGT1 may play a role in R protein accumulation [ 11 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_300="Rar1 and Sgt1 genes are required in various R - gene mediated resistance against viral , bacterial , oomycete or fungal pathogens [ 12 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_301="However , none of the previously studied R genes showed a race - non - specific and rate - limiting resistance phenotype as the RB gene ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_302="In addition , the role the Rar1 and Sgt1 genes are not universal and these genes are not essential for resistance involving some R genes [ 12 , 13 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_303="Besides the two broad - spectrum resistance genes RB and Rpi - blb2 , several race - specific late blight resistance genes have also been cloned [ 14 - 16 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_304="Numerous late blight resistance genes have recently been mapped in various potato species or populations [ 17 - 25 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_305="However , there is almost no information available about the resistance pathways mediated by any of these genes ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_306="As an initial effort to understand the RB - mediated late blight resistance pathway , we silenced the Rar1 and Sgt1 genes using an RNAi - based approach in a potato line containing the RB gene ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_307="We demonstrated that SGT1 , but not RAR1 , is essential for the RB - mediated broad - spectrum resistance to potato late blight ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS

test_315="BV / TV , Conn . D , and Tb . N decreased during the experiment and SMI and Tb . Sp increased ."

test_316="Both Tb . Th and Tb . N decreased within 2 weeks , indicating that both thinning and complete resorption of trabeculae started directly after OVX ."

test_553="Assessment of various forms of bevavioural addictions"
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_554="A first approach for the comprehensive and standardized assessment of different forms of behavioural addictions ( e . g . , pathological gambling , workaholism , compulsive buying ) is the German self - assessment questionnaire " Fragebogen zur Differenzierten Anamnese exzessiver Verhaltensweisen " ( FDAV , Questionnaire on Differentiated Assessment of Excessive Behaviours ) [ 96 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_555="The FDAV is based on the criteria of substance - related addictions , pathological gambling and impulse control disorders of the ICD - 10 [ 3 ] and the DSM - IV - TR [ 2 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_556="The FDAV is a modified version of the " Fragebogen zur Differenzierten Drogenanamnese " ( FDDA ; Questionnaire on Differentiated Assessment of Addiction , QDAA ) [ 97 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_557="Its seven modules obtain " sociodemographic information " ( e . g . , age , profession , marital status ) , " history of excessive behaviour " ( e . g . , diagnostic criteria for addictions and impulse control disorder , individual patterns of behaviour , craving symptoms ) , " critical life events " ( stress caused by traumatic events ) , " legal situation " , " medical history " , " physical and psychological complaints " , and " emotional state " ( triggering psychological conditions , or consequences of the addictive behaviour , respectively ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_558="Every module can be administered separately according to the suspected behavioural addiction , thereby making the FDAV an economical tool in assessing behavioural addictions ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_559="The FDAV is suitable for diagnostics , evaluation of therapy and follow - up in clinical practice and research ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_560="Currently , the FDAV is being validated in clinical and non - clinical samples ."

 test_detections= []

test_786="Historical Background of PTSD"
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_787="PTSD gained acceptance in the medical and psychiatric community after a number of studies appeared in prominent medical and psychiatric journals describing the psychiatric symptoms of soldiers who had served and fought in the Vietnam War ( Fox 1972 ; Goldsmith and Cretekos 1969 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_788="Subsequent publications described the profound psychological and emotional sequelae secondary to being exposed to extremely traumatic events such as fires , explosions , floods , torture , serious motor vehicle accidents ( MVAs ) , violent crimes , and sexual assault ( e . g . , Horowitz 1976 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_789="These publications posited that individuals with PTSD no longer felt in control of their lives , viewed the world as an unpredictable and dangerous place , lived in fear , and reported a loss of trust in a " just world . " These studies also reported that individuals with PTSD avoided thoughts or situations that might trigger traumatic memories , complained of feelings of emotional numbness , and exhibited symptoms of blunted affect ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_790="The conceptual refinements coupled with the empirical information generated by these studies significantly advanced our understanding of individuals who have been exposed to a traumatic stressor ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_791="This led in 1980 to the inclusion of the diagnostic criteria for PTSD in the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders III ( DSM - III ; American Psychiatric Association 1980 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_792="At that time , PTSD was defined as a syndrome that developed in response to a " stressor that would evoke significant symptoms of distress in almost everyone " ( p . 238 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_793="The DSM - III criteria also required that the individual who developed PTSD had to have been directly exposed to a traumatic event ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_794="The DSM - IV criteria ( APA 1994 ) significantly broadened the definition of PTSD to include ( a ) a " personal experience of an event that involves actual or threatened death or serious injury , or other threat to one ' s physical integrity " ( p . 463 ) or ( b ) witnessing a comparable traumatic event or even " learning about unexpected or violent death , serious harm , or threat of death or injury experienced by a family member or a close associate " ( p . 462 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_795="As a consequence of these modifications , the DSM - IV diagnostic criteria for PTSD have been criticized for failing to discriminate between symptoms of PTSD and normal stress reactions ( e . g . , learning about the 9 / 11 disaster ; Wakefield and Spitzer 2002 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_808="Discussion"
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_809="Our results indicate beneficial effects of motivational incentives on cognitive performance and alleviating effects on cognitive decline ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_810="These beneficial effects were evident in healthy young and older adults and in patients with Parkinson ' s disease ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_811="Young adults showed improved antisaccade preparation when a reward was at stake ; older adults and PD patients could utilize reward prospect to improve their impaired antisaccade preparation ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_812="Elderly participants and PD patients were not only better prepared by means of commonly used preparatory aids ( i . e . , more preparation time and advance information on the upcoming response ) but also by means of motivational incentives ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_813="These beneficial effects of motivational incentives on cognitive action preparation in healthy and pathological aging further support views that question the notion of monotonic deterioration of cognitive function with age ( Allen et al . , 2001 ) ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_814="They indicate that age - related declines can be modulated by emotion - cognition interactions ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_815="In line with the predominant view that cognitive control deteriorates in aging and Parkinson ' s disease , and in line with previous findings on age - related changes in antisaccade control specifically ( Eenshuistra et al . , 2004 ; Chan et al . , 2005 ; Amador et al . , 2006 ; Abel and Douglas , 2007 ) , the current results showed decline in antisaccade preparation in PD patients with severe motor symptoms as compared to healthy seniors ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_816="Mild - symptom patients and healthy elderly did not differ in antisaccade preparation ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_817="Healthy seniors showed declining antisaccade preparation as compared to young adults ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_818="Decline was evident on several oculomotor parameters and most pronounced on antisaccade onset latencies ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= [
    {
        "entity_type": "Multi-tissue_structure",
        "entity_value": "oculomotor",
        "start_position": 31,
        "end_position": 41
    }
]

test_819="In line with the notion that in general , elderly tend to prefer accuracy over speed , elderly showed no decreased antisaccade accuracy as compared to young adults ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_820="As compared to the young group , elderly and PD patients exhibited slightly , but not significantly more premature eye movements ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= [
    {
        "entity_type": "Organ",

        "end_position": 118
    }

test_823="On the one hand , the choice for medicated PD patients represents a limitation of the current study as we cannot exclude differential effects of medication on behavior ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_824="On the other hand , PD patients generally take medication in their daily routine , such that the results can be generalized to clinical practice ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_825="Exploratory analysis within the PD patient group revealed that patients with more severe motoric symptoms ( as indexed by their motoric subscore on the UPDRS ) displayed more signs of antisaccade decline , such as longer antisaccade latencies and lower accuracy compared to mildly affected patients , who initiated saccades equally fast as healthy adults ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_826="This suggests that dopaminergic medication was not sufficient to raise the patient ' s antisaccadic preparation up to the level of the healthy older adults ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_827="One intriguing observation was that despite the different extents of observed antisaccade performance decline in elderly and PD patients , reward prospect led to beneficial effects on antisaccade latency and accuracy in young , elderly , and PD patients alike ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_828="Young , elderly and PD patients benefited from reward prospect to the same extent , confirming that the expectancy of reward is a powerful mediator of cognitive control , even if cognitive control suffers from decline ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_829="The expectation of rewarding incentives thus seems to support older adults ' and PD patients ' ability to anticipate , prepare and initiate goal - directed behavior ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_830="These findings imply that despite a general decline in the action preparation system as indexed by increased antisaccade latency , action preparation processes remain susceptible to the prospect of future reward ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

 test_detections= [
    {
        "entity_type": "Organism_substance",
        "entity_value": "cell lysate",

test_919="The main idea there is to first sort the peptide hits according to their scores ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_920="Then for each decoy hit , one assumes that there is just one corresponding false hit in the target database ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_921="This strategy has been used extensively [ 24 ] ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_922="ROC analyses done this way generally count false positives , which are highly homologous to the target peptides , towards true positives ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_923="This has two effects : an overcount of true positives and a undercount of false positives ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_924="As a consequence , the ROC curves will appear more impressive ."

 test_detections= []

 test_detections= []

 test_detections= []

test_1222="However , it should be considered that BS is not a plain disease risk , rather a method to rank different genotypes according to their contribution to make an individual susceptible to CD ."
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

test_1223="For instance , some of our BS are very near to 1 , nevertheless none of the considered genotypes could give a 100 % risk to develop the disease ."

 test_detections= []

 test_detections= []

test_3265="RESULTS :"
 
 # GROUND TRUTH NER DETECTIONS
 test_detections= []

 test_detections= []

 test_detections= []
